<h2 class="text-center">Pastashu (Albanian Style Eclairs)</h2>
<br />
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br /><br /><br /><br /><br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Desserts/Eclairs.webp" alt="Albanian Eclairs" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Choux Pastry</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>65g (1/2 cup) All Purpose Flour</li>
                        <li>½ Tsp Sugar</li>
                        <li>½ Tsp Salt</li>
                        <li>55g (4 Tbsp) Unsalted Butter</li>
                        <li>½ cup Water</li>
                        <li>2 Eggs</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Cream Filling</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>3/4 Cup Whole Milk</li>
                        <li>1/4 Cup Sugar</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp All Purpose Flour</li>
                        <li>1 Tbsp Corn Flour</li>
                        <li>Pinch of Salt</li>
                        <li>2 Egg Yolks</li>
                        <li>½ Tsp Vanilla Extract</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Chocolate Icing</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>2 Tbsp Chocolate</li>
                        <li>4 Tbsp Heavy Cream</li>
                        <li>8 Whole Pecans and 8 Chopped Pecans (Optional)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>To Make the Pastry</h3></div>
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            In a bowl  mix the flour, sugar, salt and set aside. Then in a saucepan, heat the butter and water and let it come to boil. Remove from heat, add the flour and stir continuously until combined. Put it back on low heat and stir until the dough comes away from the sides of the pan. Let it cool down for 5 minutes and add 1 egg at a time and stir until mixed well. Do this for rest of the eggs. Finally, place the mix into a piping bag and pipe 8 lines of dough spaced apart onto a tray with baking parchment and bake for 15 minutes.
                            <br /><br />
                            <div class="text-left"><h3>To Make the Filling</h3></div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Whilst the eclairs are cooling mix the sugar, flour and salt in a bowl. Add the Egg Yolks and combine into a paste, warm the milk (but don't boil). Pour the milk little by little into the egg mixture and combine, continue this until all the milk is used and stir in the vanilla extract. Put back on heat and stir to form a thick cream, let it cool completely and pipe into the cooled eclairs.
                            <br /><br />
                            <div class="text-left"><h3>To Make the Chocolate Icing</h3></div>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Heat the cream, pour onto the chocolate and mix until the chocolate is melted and fully combined with the cream then let it cool. Dip each eclair into the chocolate so that only the top is covered (optionally finish with a sprinkle of finely chopped pecans and top with a whole pecan for extra decoration) and serve with coffee or tea.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

