<h2 class="text-center">Shendetlie (Honey and Nut Cake)</h2>
<br/>
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Desserts/Sponge_Cake.webp" alt="Sponge Cake" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Pastry</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>300g Sugar</li>
                        <li>3 Eggs</li>
                        <li>180g Melted Butter</li>
                        <li>700g Flour</li>
                        <li>100g Walnuts</li>
                        <li>4 Tbsp Honey</li>
                        <li>1 Tsp Baking Soda</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Sugar Syrup</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>220g Sugar</li>
                        <li>440ml Water</li>
                        <li>Flaked Almonds (Optional)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            In a mixing bowl cream together the eggs, sugar and cooled melted butter then add the honey and soda. Add half the flour and the walnuts (you can add the walnuts whole or ground them) and mix well. Add the rest of the flour and using your hands kneed the mixture together until a firm dough is formed. Coat a circular baking tray with olive oil. Add the dough and press it down so that it fits the whole tray, bake at 180 degrees for 35 minutes. Remove from the oven and leave to cool while making the syrup.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            To make the syrup add the sugar and water to a saucepan and bring to the boil. Leave it to boil for 10 minutes, mixing occasionally then remove from the heat.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Cut into squares (or diamonds) and pour over the hot syrup leave to soak for at least 1 hour before serving, if using add the almonds whilst the syrup is cooling so they cling to the syrup.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

