<h2 class="text-center">Flija (Layered Pancakes)</h2>
<br />
<div class="smaller-space"></div>
<div class="container-fluid well well-lg">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-12">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <br /><br /><br /><br /><br />
                    <img class="img-responsive" src="~/Images/Albania/Desserts/Pancakes.webp" alt="Pancakes" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="text-left"><h2>Ingredients</h2></div>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>For the Pancake Batter</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>500g Flour</li>
                        <li>½ Litre Water</li>
                        <li>½ Tsp Salt</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>Pancake Filling (Option 1)</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>110g Melted Butter</li>
                        <li>100ml Vegetable Oil</li>
                        <li>2 ½ Tbsp Greek Yogurt</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>Pancake Filling (Option 2)</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>110g Melted Butter</li>
                        <li>100ml Vegetable Oil</li>
                        <li>1 ½ Tbsp Clotted Cream</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                    <div class="text-left"><h3>Pancake Filling (Option 3)</h3></div>
                    <ul>
                        <li>110g Melted Butter</li>
                        <li>250ml Sour Cream</li>
                        <li>1 ½  Tbsp Olive Oil</li>
                    </ul>
                    <br />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <h2 class="text-center">Method</h2>
                    <br />
                    <ol class="text-justify">
                        <li>
                            Make the batter by mixing the flour, water and salt ensuring all the lumps are dissolved. The mixture should be thick but still of a pouring consistency, add a little extra water if required and put to one side.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            For the filling mix the butter, oil and chosen yogurt or cream ensuring all the lumps are dissolved. The mixture should be runny, leave to rest for 10 minutes before given it another good mix. The consistency should then be similar to custard, put to one side.
                            <br /><br />
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Preheat the gill to medium, take a circular pan and rub some olive oil over the base. Make the first layer of flour batter by using a squirty bottle or ladle, don't try to pour it in as it will be too thick in the pan. Place under the grill until golden brown, this will take between 3 - 5 minutes.
                            <br/><br/>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Remove from under the grill and using a brush or the back of spoon rub over the whole pan with a layer of the batter filling. Then, add a layer of the flour filling, place under the grill until golden brown, this will take between 3 - 5 minutes. Repeat until all the batter and filling has been used, then serve warm with fruit and honey.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

